headline.main: DOUBT LENINGRAD SEIZURE; Pro-Nazi Correspondent Holds Cost of Capture Is Too Great

lead_paragraph: STOCKHOLM, Sweden, Oct. 5 -- That the Germans intend to abandon the offensive against Leningrad is reported today from Berlin by the correspondent of the Stockholm Tidningen, whose dispatches often seem to be inspired by the Wilhelmstrasse.
